laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast
laboratory_examinations.findings: Hyodense lesion in the tail of the pancreas measuring 2.4 x 1.3 x 1.7 cm, mild PD dilatation up to 3mm, 1.2 x 3.6 x 5.4 cm fluid density collection, no biliary dilatation noted.
Multiple small cysts in the tail measuring 3.0 x 1.9 cm, appear to connect to the PD, mild associated dilatation of the PD up to 3mm.
Negative for CMV IgM antibody by EIA; interpretation indicates infection at undetermined time.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: If current infection is suspected, submit follow-up serum in 2-3 weeks.
